body:
I implemented most of the comments. The only pending modification is about avoid fusion. To avoid this, I tested the following:

```
      PCollection<T> output = input.apply(Create.of(query))
          .apply(ParDo.of(new ReadFn<>(dataSourceConfiguration, rowMapper)));

      PCollection<KV<Integer, T>> intermediate1 = output
          .apply(WithKeys.of(new SerializableFunction<T, Integer>() {
            public Integer apply(T record) {
              Random random = new Random();
              return random.nextInt();
            }
          }));

      PCollection<KV<Integer, Iterable<T>>> intermediate2 = intermediate1
          .apply(GroupByKey.<Integer, T>create());


      PCollection<Iterable<T>> intermediate3 = intermediate2
          .apply(Values.<Iterable<T>>create());

      output = intermediate3
          .apply(Flatten.<T>iterables());

      return output;
```

The `WithKeys` transform creates `PCollection` of `KV<Integer, T>`. It requires to define a coder. So, I tried to define `.setCoder(KVCoder.<Integer, T>of(SerializableCoder.of(Integer.class), SerializableCoder.of(T))`. However, `SerializableCoder` doesn't directly accept a generic. So I would have to create a wrapper class on top of `T`. I'm looking for a better way.
